sql:
SELECT AVG(t.energy) AS average_energy
FROM tracks t
INNER JOIN play_history p ON t.track_id = p.track_id;

SELECT track_title
FROM tracks
WHERE popularity > 50 AND energy > (SELECT AVG(energy) FROM tracks);

external_knowledge:
- The phrase 'crown jewels of music' is a metaphorical expression referring to the most highly-rated tracks; 
- 'top 10 tracks with the highest accolades' implies the tracks with the highest average ratings; 
- 'creators' refers to the artists associated with the tracks; 
- 'the albums they belong to' corresponds to the album names associated with the tracks.

sql:
SELECT track_id
FROM play_history
WHERE play_duration = (SELECT MAX(play_duration) FROM play_history);

external_knowledge:
'Cats 1983 Broadway Cast' refers to the cast of the 1983 Broadway production of the musical "Cats"; 
The ratings given by users range from 1 to 5, with 5 being the highest rating;
A play count greater than 0 indicates that a track has been played at least once.

Track ID 0 refers to a specific song in the database; 
The number of times a track has been played is determined by the count of entries in the play_history table where the track_id matches; 
The average rating of a track is calculated by averaging all ratings given to that track in the ratings table.
